Plot.
The members of Led Zeppelin are called back from vacation by manager Peter 
Grant to play Madison Square Garden. The film is enhanced by each of the 
band member's personal fantasies (hallucinations?), such as the opening 
scene (which is awfully confusing the first time around) in which Peter 
Grant, dressed in a 1930s black gangster suit drives a 1930s black Ford 
to a house and blasts everyone with a machine gun.
